# Dex OIDC provider — false positives from broken go.mod versioning.
#
# Dex declares its module as github.com/dexidp/dex without a /v2 suffix
# despite being at major version 2. Go resolves this as v0.0.0-*, causing
# scanners to report all historical CVEs as unfixed. The actual pinned
# commit (v2.45.1, 11d2eeb52b42) includes all fixes.
#
# See: ADR-0036 (docs/adr/0036-embedded-dex-identity.md)
# See: https://github.com/dexidp/dex/issues/2942

# CVE-2020-26290 — XML encoding issues (fixed in Dex v2.27.0)
CVE-2020-26290

# CVE-2020-27847 — Authentication bypass (fixed in Dex v2.27.0)
CVE-2020-27847

# CVE-2022-39222 — MitM ID token capture via intercepted auth code (fixed in Dex v2.35.0)
CVE-2022-39222

# GHSA equivalents (Trivy may use either identifier)
GHSA-m9hp-7r99-94h5
GHSA-2x32-jm95-2cpx
GHSA-vh7g-p26c-j2cw

# GO-2024-2476 — Dex TLS config discarding (no upstream fix; not applicable
# because embedded Dex serves HTTP behind the gateway, Caddy terminates TLS)
GHSA-gr79-9v6v-gc9r
